WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.891 --> 00:00:20.061
[car engine revving]

2
00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:37.120
[car engine stops]

3
00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:52.093
[indistinct music playing
on radio]

4
00:00:54.262 --> 00:00:56.598
[exhales sharply]

5
00:00:56.681 --> 00:00:58.392
Hi.

6
00:00:58.475 --> 00:00:59.810
Is Rob in here?

7
00:00:59.893 --> 00:01:01.395
I thought you both left.

8
00:01:01.478 --> 00:01:03.272
[exhales sharply]
Mind checking the back?

9
00:01:03.355 --> 00:01:05.398
He's making me late for my cake.

10
00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:09.695
Singer:
♪ I'm gonna give you all I got ♪

11
00:01:09.778 --> 00:01:11.613
[door opens]

12
00:01:11.696 --> 00:01:13.282
Singer: ♪ So baby hold on to me ♪

13
00:01:13.365 --> 00:01:15.492
[door closes]

14
00:01:15.575 --> 00:01:18.370
Singer:
♪ Whatever will be. will be ♪

15
00:01:19.621 --> 00:01:22.332
♪ The future is ours to see ♪

16
00:01:22.415 --> 00:01:23.750
[door opens]

17
00:01:23.833 --> 00:01:25.836
Singer:
♪ When you hold on to me ♪

18
00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:28.505
♪ Oh-oh. rich man. poor man ♪

19
00:01:28.588 --> 00:01:30.882
[door closes]

20
00:01:30.965 --> 00:01:32.634
Singer: ♪ Now really don't mean
all that much ♪

21
00:01:32.717 --> 00:01:37.180
Uh. maybe. um...

22
00:01:38.682 --> 00:01:41.101
if he comes back.
tell him to take a cab home

23
00:01:41.184 --> 00:01:43.312
before his father
kicks his rear-end.

24
00:01:43.395 --> 00:01:46.106
Okay. Mrs. Piest.
Happy birthday again.

25
00:01:46.189 --> 00:01:48.316
Thanks. Kim.
[chuckles] Thank you.

26
00:01:49.401 --> 00:01:52.404
[dramatic music playing]

27
00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:07.168
Elizabeth: Is Rob here?

28
00:02:08.336 --> 00:02:09.838
What are you talking about?

29
00:02:11.214 --> 00:02:12.507
Kenneth: Mom?

30
00:02:14.342 --> 00:02:15.344
Ma?

31
00:02:15.427 --> 00:02:18.471
[ominous music playing]

32
00:02:26.771 --> 00:02:28.440
What's going on?

33
00:02:28.523 --> 00:02:30.442
[sighs] I can't find him.

34
00:02:31.735 --> 00:02:34.279
Harold:
I understand protocol. sir.

35
00:02:34.362 --> 00:02:35.781
Was in Korea.

36
00:02:35.864 --> 00:02:37.657
We cannot wait 24 hours.

37
00:02:38.658 --> 00:02:39.826
Very well. Fine.

38
00:02:41.244 --> 00:02:42.370
We'll be in touch.

39
00:02:44.581 --> 00:02:46.333
Here. Smell this.

40
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:47.751
Good girl. Okay.

41
00:02:47.834 --> 00:02:49.628
Kerry. you take Caesar
in your mom's car.

42
00:02:49.711 --> 00:02:52.422
You scour east of Wolf Road
down to Algonquin.

43
00:02:52.505 --> 00:02:53.924
Kenneth. you take Kelly west.

44
00:02:54.007 --> 00:02:55.634
I'll take everything south
down to O'Hare.

45
00:02:55.717 --> 00:02:57.219
What about me? What should I do?

46
00:02:57.302 --> 00:02:58.470
Stay here.

47
00:02:58.553 --> 00:03:00.806
In case he calls
or comes back home.

48
00:03:00.889 --> 00:03:03.308
Check in with your mom.
Kenneth. every 40 minutes.

49
00:03:03.391 --> 00:03:05.352
Kerry. every 45.
I'm 50. Understood?

50
00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:09.189
-I don't have any change.
-Just... call collect.

51
00:03:09.272 --> 00:03:10.565
Come on. girl.

52
00:03:13.735 --> 00:03:14.944
[exhales sharply]

53
00:03:17.822 --> 00:03:19.908
[car door opens]

54
00:03:21.409 --> 00:03:22.911
[car door closes]

55
00:03:22.994 --> 00:03:24.496
[car engine starts]

56
00:03:32.962 --> 00:03:35.298
[telephone ringing]

57
00:03:38.802 --> 00:03:40.261
Goes to Maine West?

58
00:03:41.596 --> 00:03:43.515
Mine too. Sophomore?

59
00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:49.730
As you were saying.
he works at the pharmacy?

60
00:03:49.813 --> 00:03:52.482
-Yeah. He stocks shelves.
-Uh-hmm.

61
00:03:52.565 --> 00:03:53.859
Elizabeth went in to pick him up

62
00:03:53.942 --> 00:03:55.944
the same time as she always does
every night.

63
00:03:56.027 --> 00:03:59.698
and Rob told her that he needed
to meet a man about a job.

64
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:04.328
Who? Harold: Didn't give a name.

65
00:04:04.411 --> 00:04:06.413
He's a contractor.
He worked at construction.

66
00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:07.873
And Elizabeth told Rob

67
00:04:07.956 --> 00:04:09.458
that she'd wait for him
inside the store.

68
00:04:09.541 --> 00:04:10.625
In the car.

69
00:04:12.460 --> 00:04:14.295
I. I told him
I'd wait in the car.

70
00:04:15.630 --> 00:04:17.007
Details matter. don't they?

71
00:04:17.090 --> 00:04:18.466
Yeah.

72
00:04:19.968 --> 00:04:21.845
Inside. outside. you know...

73
00:04:23.763 --> 00:04:26.350
My wife is upset.
as you can imagine.

74
00:04:26.433 --> 00:04:28.393
[sniffles]

75
00:04:28.476 --> 00:04:29.769
Lt. Kozenczak: He's got a job.

76
00:04:31.438 --> 00:04:33.774
So what's he meeting
with this guy for?

77
00:04:33.857 --> 00:04:35.400
He's getting his license
this year.

78
00:04:35.483 --> 00:04:36.860
Saving up for a car.

79
00:04:38.903 --> 00:04:41.448
Lt. Kozenczak: All right.

80
00:04:41.531 --> 00:04:42.741
All right. Well. listen.
we have the file.

81
00:04:42.824 --> 00:04:46.369
but they usually show up. kids.

82
00:04:48.955 --> 00:04:50.749
This is Des Plaines.
It's not Mayberry.

83
00:04:50.832 --> 00:04:52.751
I'm guessing he had an itch.
He went down to Chicago...

84
00:04:52.834 --> 00:04:55.754
Harold: No. no.
Lt. Kozenczak:...met... no?

85
00:04:55.837 --> 00:04:57.923
Mr. Piest...
-Sir. he would not do that.

86
00:04:58.006 --> 00:04:58.966
Lt. Kozenczak:
I've been chief of detectives

87
00:04:59.049 --> 00:05:00.592
for a few months now.

88
00:05:00.675 --> 00:05:02.386
Before that.
I was on the street.

89
00:05:02.469 --> 00:05:05.388
Every parent who comes in
or cares enough to come in.

90
00:05:06.514 --> 00:05:07.682
we get the same response.

91
00:05:08.975 --> 00:05:10.852
One of two things
ends up happening here.

92
00:05:13.021 --> 00:05:16.692
Either. A. they get picked up
by us for doing something dumb

93
00:05:16.775 --> 00:05:18.735
or. B. they walk through
the front door

94
00:05:18.818 --> 00:05:20.612
and they get grounded.

95
00:05:20.695 --> 00:05:22.447
Okay?

96
00:05:22.530 --> 00:05:24.366
Harold: He's an honor student.

97
00:05:24.449 --> 00:05:26.368
Two badges away
from being an Eagle Scout.

98
00:05:27.702 --> 00:05:29.955
My son would not leave
his mother

99
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:32.916
sitting in a freezing
parking lot on her birthday.

100
00:05:32.999 --> 00:05:34.459
Do you understand?

101
00:05:34.542 --> 00:05:36.128
If Rob said he would be back
in a minute.

102
00:05:36.211 --> 00:05:37.421
he would be.

103
00:05:37.504 --> 00:05:39.923
You're going to interview the.

104
00:05:40.006 --> 00:05:45.095
uh. the contractor. right?

105
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:47.598
We're gonna review this file

106
00:05:47.681 --> 00:05:49.683
and we're gonna figure out
what the next steps are.

107
00:05:51.976 --> 00:05:54.813
So please go home
and get some sleep.

108
00:05:54.896 --> 00:05:56.898
Do not go running around
with your dogs anymore.

109
00:05:59.067 --> 00:06:00.527
We'll take it from here.

110
00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:06.741
Hey. Hey. Let's go.

111
00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:13.832
I can't find my gym shoe.

112
00:06:13.915 --> 00:06:15.626
Shoe? You only got one of 'em?

113
00:06:15.709 --> 00:06:17.002
Yeah.

114
00:06:17.085 --> 00:06:18.753
Eat your breakfast.

115
00:06:20.088 --> 00:06:21.798
[exhales sharply]

116
00:06:21.881 --> 00:06:23.425
Good morning.

117
00:06:27.637 --> 00:06:29.765
[exhales sharply]

118
00:06:29.848 --> 00:06:31.182
Goodnight.

119
00:06:36.104 --> 00:06:38.899
Tell the boy he left
a fucking shoe in the yard.

120
00:06:38.982 --> 00:06:40.484
You didn't wanna bring it in?

121
00:06:40.567 --> 00:06:42.611
Helen: If I bent down.
I couldn't have got back up.

122
00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:45.697
[indistinct chatter]

123
00:07:06.885 --> 00:07:08.011
Yeah?

124
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:09.637
Why is this on my desk?

125
00:07:11.264 --> 00:07:13.183
I would've put it in your hand
if it'd been there.

126
00:07:13.266 --> 00:07:15.602
Helen had an overnight.

127
00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:17.229
You try getting that little shit
ready for school.

128
00:07:17.312 --> 00:07:18.980
out the door. and be on time.

129
00:07:20.523 --> 00:07:22.609
I got kids too. I was on time.

130
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:25.445
Oh. yeah? Were they even awake
when you left?

131
00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:27.823
-No.
-[scoffs]

132
00:07:27.906 --> 00:07:30.450
You don't do shit.
Shut the fuck up.

133
00:07:30.533 --> 00:07:31.910
Do me a favor.
Take a look at this.

134
00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:33.078
Det. Tovar: Yeah. I did.

135
00:07:33.161 --> 00:07:34.871
Missing kid. So what?

136
00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:36.831
Just took off last night.

137
00:07:37.916 --> 00:07:40.460
Okay. So you want me to bump
you back to narcotics right now

138
00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:42.504
or you want me to wait
till the end of the day?

139
00:07:44.673 --> 00:07:46.633
You ain't gotta be
so mean about it.

140
00:07:47.884 --> 00:07:49.469
Was gonna say yes.

141
00:07:49.552 --> 00:07:51.012
Uh-hmm.

142
00:07:52.681 --> 00:07:53.848
You look good. by the way.

143
00:07:55.016 --> 00:07:56.727
[slurps]

144
00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:57.811
I know.

145
00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:08.488
Kim Byers?

146
00:08:08.571 --> 00:08:09.698
Yes. sir?

147
00:08:11.032 --> 00:08:13.535
Detective Tovar.
How are you doing?

148
00:08:13.618 --> 00:08:15.621
I'm fine. sir. How are you?

149
00:08:15.704 --> 00:08:21.126
Uh. you worked
with Rob Piest yesterday. huh?

150
00:08:21.209 --> 00:08:22.544
Yes. sir.

151
00:08:24.754 --> 00:08:25.839
You're not a suspect.

152
00:08:25.922 --> 00:08:27.049
Okay.

153
00:08:27.132 --> 00:08:28.592
Unless you should be?

154
00:08:28.675 --> 00:08:29.760
No.

155
00:08:29.843 --> 00:08:31.762
Did he run away?

156
00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:34.014
Go to the city?
Got friends there?

157
00:08:34.097 --> 00:08:35.807
Know anything
about anything like that?

158
00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:38.226
No. No. And he wouldn't.

159
00:08:38.309 --> 00:08:39.770
You're so sure?

160
00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:41.521
That's not him.

161
00:08:41.604 --> 00:08:42.647
What's him?

162
00:08:43.815 --> 00:08:45.734
A little nerdy.

163
00:08:46.901 --> 00:08:48.862
He's a good-looking nerd.

164
00:08:48.945 --> 00:08:50.030
You two a thing?

165
00:08:54.075 --> 00:08:55.535
Before his mother came
to pick him up.

166
00:08:55.618 --> 00:08:57.621
before he disappeared.
what happened?

167
00:08:57.704 --> 00:09:00.248
A contractor came in here.
I have his card.

168
00:09:00.331 --> 00:09:02.834
I took it out of the drawer
in case somebody asked.

169
00:09:11.426 --> 00:09:13.011
So he was here?

170
00:09:13.094 --> 00:09:15.347
Kim: Measuring some things
for some work he was gonna do.

171
00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:16.848
Rob was gonna talk to him
about a job.

172
00:09:16.931 --> 00:09:18.809
so he took his coat back
from me and left.

173
00:09:18.892 --> 00:09:20.185
That's the last time I saw him.

174
00:09:20.268 --> 00:09:21.561
Why'd you have his coat?

175
00:09:21.644 --> 00:09:22.896
The door. Always opening.

176
00:09:22.979 --> 00:09:25.315
I was freezing.
so he lent it to me.

177
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:27.317
Did you talk to this guy?

178
00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:29.736
Kim: He did a job here
a few months back.

179
00:09:29.819 --> 00:09:32.281
But he isn't really nice
to girls.

180
00:09:32.364 --> 00:09:34.700
Isn't nice to girls.

181
00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:36.201
I don't know. Just a feeling.

182
00:09:36.284 --> 00:09:38.328
He was kinda mean.

183
00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:41.707
Not just to me.
all the girls who work here.

184
00:09:41.790 --> 00:09:43.291
He was nice to the boys.

185
00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:48.004
[ominous music playing]

186
00:09:58.682 --> 00:10:00.350
[car engine stops]

187
00:10:07.232 --> 00:10:10.235
[♪♪♪]

188
00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:33.675
[doorbell buzzes]

189
00:11:04.205 --> 00:11:05.791
[pounding]

190
00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:07.876
Police. Looking for John Gacy.

191
00:11:19.346 --> 00:11:20.722
Can I help you?

192
00:11:22.307 --> 00:11:23.725
Rafael Tovar.

193
00:11:25.060 --> 00:11:26.061
You wanna hang up?

194
00:11:28.146 --> 00:11:30.148
Had a death in the family.

195
00:11:30.231 --> 00:11:31.483
My uncle.

196
00:11:31.566 --> 00:11:33.026
Oh. I'm sorry to hear that.

197
00:11:33.109 --> 00:11:35.487
Yeah. Was expected. a little.

198
00:11:35.570 --> 00:11:37.030
But I got my sister on the line.

199
00:11:37.113 --> 00:11:38.865
We're just trying
to figure things out.

200
00:11:38.948 --> 00:11:41.201
Well. we gotta talk.
Kid's missing.

201
00:11:41.284 --> 00:11:43.453
Reported last seen with you.

202
00:11:43.536 --> 00:11:46.999
Oh. Uh. hang on a second. Karen.

203
00:11:47.082 --> 00:11:51.503
Um. yeah.

204
00:11:51.586 --> 00:11:53.338
I don't know who that is.

205
00:11:53.421 --> 00:11:55.924
-You run PDM Contractors?
-Yeah.

206
00:11:56.007 --> 00:11:56.967
What's that stand for?

207
00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:59.720
Uh. Pretty Damn Messy?

208
00:11:59.803 --> 00:12:01.054
Polish Daily Maintenance?

209
00:12:01.137 --> 00:12:02.347
[chuckles]

210
00:12:05.058 --> 00:12:07.769
Painting. Decorating.
and Maintenance.

211
00:12:07.852 --> 00:12:09.187
You were at the Nisson Pharmacy
last night

212
00:12:09.270 --> 00:12:11.064
offering this kid a job?

213
00:12:11.147 --> 00:12:16.069
Uh. I was there
but. no. I didn't.

214
00:12:16.152 --> 00:12:18.530
I don't even know
who this kid is. but...

215
00:12:18.613 --> 00:12:20.490
Tell your sister you'll
call her back. We gotta talk.

216
00:12:20.573 --> 00:12:22.409
Did you not hear me when I said
I had a death in the family?

217
00:12:22.492 --> 00:12:23.827
I did.

218
00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:25.370
I need to get my affairs
in order.

219
00:12:26.496 --> 00:12:27.831
I need a statement.

220
00:12:31.292 --> 00:12:32.920
[chuckles]

221
00:12:33.003 --> 00:12:34.880
Of course. Of course.

222
00:12:34.963 --> 00:12:36.506
I mean. I. I don't mind.

223
00:12:36.589 --> 00:12:38.133
I'd be glad to.

224
00:12:38.216 --> 00:12:40.301
It's just could you give me
a few hours

225
00:12:41.886 --> 00:12:44.347
to handle this
and then I... I'm all yours?

226
00:12:48.977 --> 00:12:50.437
Swing by the station.

227
00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:51.813
I'll be there.

228
00:12:52.897 --> 00:12:53.898
Great.

229
00:12:55.150 --> 00:12:56.902
Condolences again.

230
00:12:56.985 --> 00:12:58.194
Appreciate you.

231
00:13:00.572 --> 00:13:03.575
[♪♪♪]

232
00:13:36.358 --> 00:13:39.361
[device beeping]

233
00:13:48.703 --> 00:13:49.830
When I showed him
the photograph.

234
00:13:49.913 --> 00:13:51.957
he said he never saw the kid.

235
00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:53.250
But he got pissed at you.

236
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:56.086
Annoyed. And I was pushing him.

237
00:13:56.169 --> 00:13:58.380
Dead uncle? I might be the same.

238
00:13:58.463 --> 00:14:00.132
What do you think?

239
00:14:00.215 --> 00:14:02.259
I think two people said
they saw them together.

240
00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:04.011
No.

241
00:14:04.094 --> 00:14:06.221
Two people said that Rob Piest
said they were together.

242
00:14:06.304 --> 00:14:08.265
Nobody saw 'em.

243
00:14:08.348 --> 00:14:09.391
What do you think?

244
00:14:11.142 --> 00:14:12.436
That I spent
enough time undercover.

245
00:14:12.519 --> 00:14:14.896
being lied to. in the eye.

246
00:14:16.147 --> 00:14:18.191
No. the kid was with him.

247
00:14:18.274 --> 00:14:20.152
And I think we need to get
a warrant for that house.

248
00:14:20.235 --> 00:14:21.569
Yeah. Yeah. it's me.

249
00:14:23.530 --> 00:14:26.032
Yeah. I need everything
that Chicago PD's got on a guy.

250
00:14:27.409 --> 00:14:29.328
And I need a favor ASAP.

251
00:14:29.411 --> 00:14:31.163
G-A-C-Y.

252
00:14:31.246 --> 00:14:32.289
Thank you. sir.

253
00:14:32.372 --> 00:14:33.415
Det. Tovar:
First name. John Wayne.

254
00:14:33.498 --> 00:14:35.125
Hello. How we doing?

255
00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:37.002
Det. Tovar: Yeah. Yeah.
-Hiya. How's it going?

256
00:14:37.085 --> 00:14:38.295
Det. Tovar:
Like Rooster Cogburn.

257
00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:39.963
Good to see you. gentlemen.

258
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:44.968
Thank you. officer.

259
00:14:45.051 --> 00:14:46.470
-Mr. Gacy.
-Hi.

260
00:14:46.553 --> 00:14:47.930
Thanks for coming in.

261
00:14:48.013 --> 00:14:49.932
This is Lieutenant
Joe Kozenczak.

262
00:14:50.015 --> 00:14:51.058
Mr. Gacy.

263
00:14:51.141 --> 00:14:52.392
Yeah. Anything to help.

264
00:14:52.475 --> 00:14:54.186
And. and John's fine.
